dancing cheek to cheek #

01:31:41.372 --> 01:31:44.068
-Thought you'd never wake up.
-What?

01:31:45.959 --> 01:31:48.545
-Where did you find that?
-I liberated it.

01:31:49.009 --> 01:31:50.197
I think that's called looting.

01:31:50.280 --> 01:31:53.133
No one should own music.
The real question is:

01:31:53.300 --> 01:31:55.336
-Who wrote the song?
-Irving Berlin.

01:31:55.420 --> 01:31:56.421
-For?
-Top Hat.

01:31:57.261 --> 01:31:58.472
Is there a song you don't know?

01:31:58.597 --> 01:32:01.078
Nope. He sings all the time.

01:32:01.975 --> 01:32:05.646
Good morning. Did you know that?
You're always singing.

01:32:05.987 --> 01:32:07.726
I've been told before.

01:32:08.732 --> 01:32:10.470
Kip's another one.

01:32:17.323 --> 01:32:19.065
'Wang Wang Blues.'

01:32:19.703 --> 01:32:20.661
You're incredible.

01:32:29.816 --> 01:32:31.505
-Good mornin', Miss.
-Hello.

01:32:32.046 --> 01:32:33.454
You saved my life.

01:32:35.285 --> 01:32:36.621
I haven't forgotten.

01:32:38.579 --> 01:32:40.660
I thought you were very, very tall.

01:32:40.973 --> 01:32:44.987
You seemed so big and... giant.

01:32:45.672 --> 01:32:48.180
I felt like a child who
can't keep her balance.

01:32:48.406 --> 01:32:51.338
-A toddler.
-A toddler.

01:33:15.602 --> 01:33:17.404
My hair was long at some point.

01:33:22.032 --> 01:33:24.643
I've forgotten what a
nuisance it is to wash.

01:33:28.221 --> 01:33:30.728
Try this. I found a great jar of it.

01:33:31.338 --> 01:33:32.184
Olive oil.

01:33:33.218 --> 01:33:34.099
Thank you.

01:33:45.103 --> 01:33:46.246
Is this for my hair?

01:33:47.312 --> 01:33:48.977
Yes, for your hair.

01:33:57.591 --> 01:34:00.260
There was a general who wore a patch...

01:34:00.344 --> 01:34:01.966
over a perfectly good eye.

01:34:04.327 --> 01:34:05.949
The men fought harder for him.

01:34:12.199 --> 01:34:14.623
Sometimes I think I
could get up and dance.

01:34:17.718 --> 01:34:18.779
What's under your mittens?

01:34:25.717 --> 01:34:26.912
What's under your mittens?

01:34:48.771 --> 01:34:50.375
He's waiting for you.

01:34:51.842 --> 01:34:53.277
I'll see you tonight?

01:34:54.641 --> 01:34:57.810
Look Moose,
we need you to stay in Tobruk.

01:34:57.894 --> 01:35:00.024
I know it's a bit of a short straw,

01:35:00.207 --> 01:35:02.307
but Jerry's got our maps, you know.

01:35:02.489 --> 01:35:05.539
And now they're getting their
spies into Cairo using our maps.

01:35:05.622 --> 01:35:07.995
They'll get Rommel into
Cairo using our maps.

01:35:08.162 --> 01:35:10.341
The whole of the desert's like a bloody
bus route,

01:35:10.424 --> 01:35:11.677
and we gave it to 'em!

01:35:11.845 --> 01:35:13.412
Any foreigner who turned up:

01:35:13.496 --> 01:35:16.378
'Welcome to the Royal Geographic.
Take our maps.'

01:35:16.462 --> 01:35:17.949
Our Madox went mad, you know.

01:35:18.363 --> 01:35:20.009
-Did you know Peter Madox?
-Yeah.

01:35:20.093 --> 01:35:22.471
Magnificent explorer. Thanks, Aicha.

01:35:22.759 --> 01:35:25.929
And after he found out he'd
been betrayed by Almasy.

01:35:26.549 --> 01:35:27.840
His best friend.

01:35:28.508 --> 01:35:30.738
Absolutely destroyed the poor sot.

01:35:50.875 --> 01:35:53.430
Hey, Commandant, stay in line!

01:36:11.330 --> 01:36:15.209
Hello, little Tommy.
Little baby, hello.

01:36:16.522 --> 01:36:18.815
-Recognize him? British friend?
-No.

01:36:20.265 --> 01:36:21.240
Aaah!

01:36:24.858 --> 01:36:26.557
-Get up!
-No!

01:36:27.151 --> 01:36:28.374
Get up at once!

01:36:28.458 --> 01:36:30.476
No, I don't have a boyfriend.

01:36:32.281 --> 01:36:34.540
I don't know anybody!

01:36:35.448 --> 01:36:36.224
Halt!

01:36:36.851 --> 01:36:40.516
No! No!

01:36:51.622 --> 01:36:52.896
David Caravaggio.

01:36:53.017 --> 01:36:53.902
No.

01:36:54.459 --> 01:36:57.035
This was taken in Cairo
at British headquarters.

01:36:57.208 --> 01:36:58.572
July '41.

01:37:00.005 --> 01:37:01.608
And so was this.

01:37:01.821 --> 01:37:04.849
August '41. And this.

01:37:05.537 --> 01:37:07.114
February '42.

01:37:08.143 --> 01:37:09.475
It's possible.

01:37:10.075 --> 01:37:12.295
I was buying or selling something.

01:37:12.379 --> 01:37:14.209
I've been to Cairo many times.

01:37:14.568 --> 01:37:17.291
You are a Canadian spy
working for the Allies.

01:37:17.416 --> 01:37:19.262
Code name: Moose.

01:37:27.878 --> 01:37:28.650
Ja?

01:37:29.370 --> 01:37:32.499
Can you get me a doctor? I'm sick.

01:37:33.740 --> 01:37:35.313
I'm leaking blood!

01:37:37.679 --> 01:37:38.508
You want a doctor?

01:37:38.686 --> 01:37:40.532
I've been askin' for weeks, months...

01:37:40.731 --> 01:37:41.746
We don't have a doctor.

01:37:43.785 --> 01:37:44.838
But we do have a nurse.

01:37:44.922 --> 01:37:47.620
Sure, great. A nurse would be great.

01:37:49.832 --> 01:37:54.346
Look, give me something.
A name, a code.

01:37:54.933 --> 01:37:56.425
So we can all get out of this room.

01:37:58.469 --> 01:38:00.235
I can't think in this heat.

01:38:01.015 --> 01:38:04.518
-It's too hot.
-I slept with a girl.

01:38:06.435 --> 01:38:08.509
I've got a wife in Tripoli.

01:38:09.761 --> 01:38:13.097
A girl comes up and points at you,
you only see trouble.

01:38:13.741 --> 01:38:14.891
Fire!

01:38:18.116 --> 01:38:19.970
I'll tell you what I'm going to do.

01:38:21.237 --> 01:38:22.505
This is your nurse, by the way.

01:38:23.023 --> 01:38:25.776
She's Muslim,
so she'll understand all of this.

01:38:26.500 --> 01:38:29.623
What's the punishment for adultery?
Let's leave it at that.

01:38:29.947 --> 01:38:32.022
You're married and you were fucking
another woman,

01:38:32.105 --> 01:38:32.978
so that's, uh...

01:38:35.770 --> 01:38:36.860
Is it the hands that are cut off?

01:38:38.117 --> 01:38:40.277
Or is that for stealing?
Does anyone know?

01:38:41.076 --> 01:38:44.044
Well, you must know.
You were brought up in Libya, yes?

01:38:44.578 --> 01:38:46.547
-Don't cut me.
-Or was it Toronto?

01:38:48.478 --> 01:38:49.550
Ten fingers.

01:38:49.717 --> 01:38:50.732
How about this?

01:38:51.319 --> 01:38:54.318
You give me a name for every finger.
It doesn't matter who.

01:38:54.702 --> 01:38:56.670
I get something, you keep something.

01:38:57.305 --> 01:39:00.005
-I'm trying to be reasonable.
-Don't cut me. Come on!

01:39:04.894 --> 01:39:06.150
Are thumbs fingers?

01:39:14.869 --> 01:39:17.228
-I get no help from these people.
-Telephone.

01:39:17.341 --> 01:39:18.771
I'm sick of this room,

01:39:18.993 --> 01:39:21.682
I'm sick of this heat and
I'm sick of this phone!

01:39:29.628 --> 01:39:31.013
Ah! The Geneva Convention!

01:39:31.097 --> 01:39:33.128
Hey, come on! You can't do that!

01:39:36.201 --> 01:39:37.504
-Come over here.
-I'll give you names.

01:39:37.588 --> 01:39:39.561
-You!
-I'll give you names!

01:39:39.933 --> 01:39:41.523
-Come on!
-What names did you say?

01:39:42.019 --> 01:39:46.409
Aaah!
Aaah! Let me think! Just let me think!

01:39:46.493 --> 01:39:49.311
I can't think!
I know them! Please, let me think!

01:39:49.395 --> 01:39:52.189
I promise! Oh, please, please, no!

01:39:52.789 --> 01:39:55.036
-What name did you say? I knew them!
-Come on!

01:39:55.120 --> 01:39:58.020
I can't think of any names!
Not my hands! Oh, dear God!

01:39:58.103 --> 01:40:01.789
-What are you waiting for?
-Jesus Christ! Jesus Christ, no!

01:40:01.914 --> 01:40:04.416
I promise! Oh, please, not my hands!

01:40:04.541 --> 01:40:08.405
No! Jesus! Jesus! Oh, dear God!

01:40:08.489 --> 01:40:10.630
-Please don't cut me!
-Come on!

01:40:10.797 --> 01:40:13.300
Aaah! No!

01:40:13.390 --> 01:40:17.270
Please don't cut!

01:40:17.354 --> 01:40:18.279
Don't!

01:40:20.557 --> 01:40:22.508
The man who took my thumbs?

01:40:24.228 --> 01:40:27.482
I found him eventually. I killed him.

01:40:28.273 --> 01:40:30.818
The man who took my photograph?
I found him too.

01:40:30.943 --> 01:40:33.383
That took me a year. He's dead.

01:40:35.239 --> 01:40:37.010
Another man showed the Germans...

01:40:37.094 --> 01:40:39.414
a way to get their spies into Cairo.

01:40:40.504 --> 01:40:41.905
I've been looking for him.

01:40:44.328 --> 01:40:46.357
You can't get through there.
It's impossible.

01:40:46.583 --> 01:40:48.919
I was looking again at Bell's old maps.

01:40:49.086 --> 01:40:50.935
If we can find a way through the Wadi,

01:40:51.019 --> 01:40:53.288
we can drive straight into Cairo.

01:40:53.611 --> 01:40:55.586
This whole spur is a real possibility.

01:40:55.794 --> 01:40:57.988
So on Thursday,
you don't trust Bell's map,

01:40:58.072 --> 01:40:59.881
Bell was a fool,
Bell couldn't draw a map.

01:40:59.965 --> 01:41:01.784
But on Friday,
he's suddenly infallible.

01:41:02.683 --> 01:41:05.560
-And where are the expedition maps?
-In my room.

01:41:06.068 --> 01:41:08.022
Those maps belong to His
Majesty's government.

01:41:08.146 --> 01:41:09.220
They shouldn't be left lying around

01:41:09.304 --> 01:41:11.192
for any Tom,
Dick or Harry to have sight of.

01:41:12.252 --> 01:41:13.610
What on earth's the matter with you?

01:41:13.895 --> 01:41:16.406
Don't be so bloody naive!
You know there's a war breaking out!

01:41:24.525 --> 01:41:25.993
This arrived this morning.

01:41:26.412 --> 01:41:28.011
'By order of the British Government,

01:41:28.095 --> 01:41:32.391
all international expeditions
to be aborted by May, 1939.'

01:41:36.300 --> 01:41:38.308
What do they care about our maps?

01:41:40.040 --> 01:41:41.492
What do we find in the desert?

01:41:42.589 --> 01:41:44.357
Arrowheads, spears.

01:41:45.571 --> 01:41:47.936
In a war, if you own the desert,
you own North Africa.

01:41:48.103 --> 01:41:49.914
Own the desert? Ha!

01:41:52.021 --> 01:41:55.539
Um, Madox? That place...

01:41:58.075 --> 01:42:01.120
That place at the base
of a woman's throat.

01:42:03.153 --> 01:42:05.304
You know, the hollow here.

01:42:06.816 --> 01:42:09.026
Does it have an official name?

01:42:10.862 --> 01:42:14.623
For God's sake,
man, pull yourself together.

01:42:25.299 --> 01:42:27.810
Nowhere is there any wild
patriotic excitement,

01:42:28.094 --> 01:42:30.260
but everywhere there is
a deep hatred of war.

01:42:30.446 --> 01:42:32.250
The answer lies with one man,

01:42:32.616 --> 01:42:35.660
and the solid mass of the
crowd surging round his car...

01:42:35.744 --> 01:42:38.167
are a symbol of the fact
that the British people

01:42:38.251 --> 01:42:40.322
are more firmly of one mind today...

01:42:40.406 --> 01:42:42.169
than at any other time in our history.

01:42:49.687 --> 01:42:53.350
There's a great to-do in San Down Bay,
with rowing and sailing,

01:42:53.534 --> 01:42:55.904
and no end of sport
for every water baby.

01:42:58.803 --> 01:42:59.756
Sorry.

01:43:04.263 --> 01:43:06.521
I can't... I can't do this.

01:43:10.500 --> 01:43:12.889
I can't do this.
I can't do this any more.

01:43:42.426 --> 01:43:43.548
I'd better go now.

01:43:47.611 --> 01:43:48.704
Say goodbye here.

01:43:49.047 --> 01:43:50.115
I'm not agreeing.

01:43:51.542 --> 01:43:53.503
Don't think I'm agreeing,
because I'm not.

01:43:54.097 --> 01:43:55.672
Any minute now, he'll find out.

01:43:55.756 --> 01:43:57.522
We'll barge into someone.
It'll kill him.

01:43:57.608 --> 01:43:59.405
Don't go over it again, please.

01:44:12.646 --> 01:44:13.369
Katharine?

01:44:17.544 --> 01:44:18.231
I...

01:44:19.505 --> 01:44:21.241
I just want you to know I'm...

01:44:22.675 --> 01:44:23.981
I'm not missing you yet.

01:44:27.780 --> 01:44:31.192
You will. You will.

01:45:05.767 --> 01:45:07.202
I believe I'm rather late.

01:45:08.262 --> 01:45:10.944
Good. We're all here.

01:45:11.284 --> 01:45:14.646
A toast to the International Sand Club.

01:45:15.428 --> 01:45:17.009
May it soon resurface.

01:45:17.294 --> 01:45:19.129
The International Sand Club.

01:45:19.422 --> 01:45:24.344
The International Sand Club: misfits,
buggers, fascists and fools.

01:45:24.711 --> 01:45:27.113
God bless us, every one. Oops!

01:45:27.525 --> 01:45:31.202
Mustn't say 'International.'
Dirty word, filthy word.

01:45:31.448 --> 01:45:34.121
His Majesty, die Fuhrer, il duce...

01:45:34.288 --> 01:45:35.664
Sorry. What's your point?

01:45:36.612 --> 01:45:38.833
And the people here don't want us.
You must be joking.

01:45:38.917 --> 01:45:41.956
Egyptians are desperate to get rid of
the colonials.

01:45:42.155 --> 01:45:43.742
Isn't that right, Fouad?

01:45:44.009 --> 01:45:46.912
Some of their best people getting
down on their hands and knees,

01:45:46.996 --> 01:45:48.761
begging to be spared the Knighthood.

01:45:49.097 --> 01:45:52.227
Isn't that right?
Hmm? Isn't that right, Sir Ronnie?

01:45:53.733 --> 01:45:56.268
What's my point?
Oh, I've invented a new dance.

01:45:56.352 --> 01:45:57.935
Anybody up for it? It's called...

01:45:58.520 --> 01:46:00.286
It's called the Bosphorus Hug.

01:46:02.500 --> 01:46:03.340
Madox?

01:46:03.734 --> 01:46:06.705
Or Bermann? You'll dance with me? Hmm?

01:46:08.482 --> 01:46:10.324
Dag. Come on, Daggers.

01:46:10.449 --> 01:46:12.564
Let's eat first. Sit down.

01:46:15.788 --> 01:46:19.124
# We'll bathe at Brighton
The fish you'll frighten #

01:46:19.249 --> 01:46:21.919
# When you're in your
bathing suit so thin #

01:46:22.086 --> 01:46:24.770
We'll make the shellfish
grin Fin to fin #

01:46:24.854 --> 01:46:27.705
They're playing it far too slowly,
but these were the words,

01:46:27.841 --> 01:46:30.481
actually, before they were cleaned up.

01:46:31.679 --> 01:46:35.133
Might be a song for you, Mrs. Clif...

01:46:35.217 --> 01:46:37.343
You either shut up or go home!
You're completely blasted!

01:46:37.427 --> 01:46:39.825
-Sit down!
-Absolutely right! Shut up! Shut up!

01:46:40.693 --> 01:46:43.630
Sorry. Sorry. I'm so sorry.

01:46:43.866 --> 01:46:45.654
I can't think what came over me.

01:46:47.486 --> 01:46:49.278
Lashings of apologies...

01:46:50.445 --> 01:46:51.522
all around.

01:47:25.488 --> 01:47:26.617
Thank you.

01:47:36.827 --> 01:47:40.080
-Why were you holding his collar?
-What?

01:47:40.164 --> 01:47:43.763
'What'? That boy. That little boy.

01:47:43.847 --> 01:47:45.355
You were holding his collar.

01:47:45.438 --> 01:47:47.017
You were gripping his collar. What for?

01:47:47.193 --> 01:47:49.032
Hmm? Is he next?

01:47:49.465 --> 01:47:52.304
Are you going to drag him into
your little room? Where is it?

01:47:52.548 --> 01:47:53.281
Is this it?

01:47:53.438 --> 01:47:54.825
Don't do this.

01:47:55.613 --> 01:47:58.646
I've watched you.
I've watched you at garden parties,

01:47:58.730 --> 01:48:00.899
on verandas, at the races.

01:48:01.167 --> 01:48:04.876
-How can you... stand there?
-Please.

01:48:05.314 --> 01:48:08.108
How can you ever smile,

01:48:08.233 --> 01:48:11.938
as if your life hadn't capsized?

01:48:13.947 --> 01:48:14.917
You know why?

01:48:19.036 --> 01:48:20.299
Dance with me.

01:48:22.081 --> 01:48:22.795
No.

01:48:24.612 --> 01:48:25.950
Dance with me.

01:48:27.586 --> 01:48:29.024
I want to touch you.

01:48:30.589 --> 01:48:33.552
I want the things which are mine,
which belong to me.

01:48:37.888 --> 01:48:40.183
Do you think you're the
only one who feels anything?

01:48:41.475 --> 01:48:42.591
Is that what you think?

01:49:03.519 --> 01:49:04.779
Why don't you go?

01:49:06.642 --> 01:49:10.229
-Get some sleep.
-Would you like me to?

01:49:17.220 --> 01:49:18.003
Good night.

01:50:24.621 --> 01:50:25.376
Hana.

01:50:31.335 --> 01:50:32.083
Kip.

01:51:07.788 --> 01:51:10.402
Just wait. Don't look at anything yet.

01:51:34.412 --> 01:51:35.188
Wait.

01:51:52.290 --> 01:51:53.172
Kip!

01:53:15.170 --> 01:53:16.934
Oh, thank you!

01:53:18.293 --> 01:53:19.318
Mmm!

01:53:34.059 --> 01:53:37.114
If one night I didn't come to see you,

01:53:39.523 --> 01:53:40.941
what would you do?

01:53:42.278 --> 01:53:44.137
I'd try not to expect you.

01:53:47.865 --> 01:53:51.261
Yes, but if it got late and...

01:53:52.036 --> 01:53:53.424
I hadn't shown up?

01:53:56.154 --> 01:53:58.792
Then I'd think there must be a reason.

01:54:00.544 --> 01:54:02.135
You wouldn't come to find me?

01:54:05.398 --> 01:54:08.376
Hmm.
That makes me never want to come here.

01:54:13.946 --> 01:54:15.447
Then I'd tell myself,

01:54:16.060 --> 01:54:17.828
he spends all day searching.

01:54:19.396 --> 01:54:21.565
In the night, he wants to be found.

01:54:27.851 --> 01:54:30.729
I do. I do want you to find me.

01:54:31.888 --> 01:54:33.273
I do want to be found.

01:54:51.805 --> 01:54:54.223
I was looking for Lieutenant Singh.

01:54:54.390 --> 01:54:57.415
-He's sleeping.
-Only we've got to go to work.

01:54:58.706 --> 01:54:59.677
I'll tell him.

01:55:02.271 --> 01:55:04.774
What is it? Is it a mine?

01:55:04.858 --> 01:55:06.762
It's a bomb by a viaduct.

01:55:08.904 --> 01:55:11.361
-Does he have to go?
-Beg pardon?

01:55:11.773 --> 01:55:13.160
What if you couldn't find him?

01:55:13.558 --> 01:55:15.808
Sergeant, not today. Not this morning.

01:55:16.447 --> 01:55:18.766
-What's happening? Am I needed?
-Afraid so, Sir.

01:55:22.062 --> 01:55:23.711
Don't go. I'm frightened.

01:55:25.002 --> 01:55:26.277
This is what I do.

01:55:26.879 --> 01:55:28.416
I do this every day.

01:55:49.379 --> 01:55:50.173
Hardy!

01:55:50.470 --> 01:55:54.025
Serial number K-K-I-P...

01:55:55.031 --> 01:55:56.910
2-6-0-0.

01:55:57.036 --> 01:55:59.913
K-K-I-P 2600, Sir!

01:56:00.334 --> 01:56:01.281
I'll get the oxygen.

01:57:00.940 --> 01:57:02.323
Hardy, what's happening?

01:57:02.407 --> 01:57:04.705
Can't see, Sir! It's from the road!

01:57:11.016 --> 01:57:13.349
Tanks, Sir!
I don't know what it's about!

01:57:13.433 --> 01:57:15.789
-Stop 'em!
-Stop!

01:57:18.784 --> 01:57:22.079
-Hardy!
-Stop! Stop!

01:57:22.163 --> 01:57:24.482
What is this, a bloody carnival?

01:57:24.566 --> 01:57:25.919
The fuse has snapped!

01:57:26.654 --> 01:57:28.780
What's happened? Is it armed?

01:57:32.644 --> 01:57:33.743
Hang on a second.

01:57:34.034 --> 01:57:34.962
I'll be right with you.

01:57:36.237 --> 01:57:37.669
Can you see the detonator, Sir?

01:57:40.416 --> 01:57:42.393
You've got to cut it, Sir.
That frost won't last.

01:57:43.434 --> 01:57:46.720
Stop! Stop! Slow down!

01:57:50.902 --> 01:57:54.125
Stop! Stop! Slow down!

01:57:54.209 --> 01:57:56.169
-Go away!
-Yes, Sir.

01:57:57.358 --> 01:57:59.927
-This is making me incredibly angry.
-I know, Sir.

01:58:02.244 --> 01:58:04.053
-Watch out! That'll burn!
-Ow!

01:58:12.268 --> 01:58:13.220
Can you feel 'em?

01:58:23.246 --> 01:58:24.326
Cut it, Sir.

01:58:25.626 --> 01:58:26.410
You've gotta cut it!

01:58:26.494 --> 01:58:28.318
I don't even know if
this is the right wire.

01:58:28.573 --> 01:58:31.576
Choose. Just choose a wire and cut it.

01:58:54.236 --> 01:58:58.354
Get a blanket!
Dade, get a blanket for Lieutenant!

01:58:58.438 --> 01:59:00.969
Sarge!
Sarge! It's over, Sir! It's over!

01:59:01.183 --> 01:59:04.233
-Jerry's surrendered!
-Yeah-ha!

01:59:10.417 --> 01:59:11.618
Sir, congratulations.

01:59:13.190 --> 01:59:16.819
# Heaven
I'm in heaven #

01:59:18.112 --> 01:59:20.497
Kip? Kip?

01:59:20.906 --> 01:59:21.821
Kip!

01:59:22.908 --> 01:59:26.382
# And my heart beats so
that I can hardly speak #

01:59:26.466 --> 01:59:31.513
# And I seem to find
the happiness I seek #

01:59:32.576 --> 01:59:34.211
Hey, we're goin' home!

01:59:34.424 --> 01:59:39.701
# When we're out together
dancing cheek to cheek #

01:59:42.807 --> 01:59:44.234
It's raining.

01:59:47.709 --> 01:59:54.541
# And the cares that hung
around me through the week #

01:59:54.773 --> 02:00:01.850
# Seem to vanish like a
gambler's lucky streak #

02:00:02.031 --> 02:00:08.392
# When we're out together
dancing cheek to cheek #

02:00:09.662 --> 02:00:13.124
# Oh, I love to climb a mountain #

02:00:13.208 --> 02:00:16.628
# And to reach the highest peak #

02:00:16.754 --> 02:00:20.830
# But it doesn't thrill
me half as much #

02:00:20.914 --> 02:00:23.927
# As dancing cheek to cheek #

02:00:27.931 --> 02:00:30.351
Kip, come and dance with us.

02:00:31.222 --> 02:00:33.800
-Later.
-Oh, come on.

02:00:37.942 --> 02:00:39.048
Clap now.

02:00:40.450 --> 02:00:41.406
Yeah.

02:01:03.934 --> 02:01:05.802
Here comes the bomb squad!

02:01:13.774 --> 02:01:15.271
Hey, let me handle it!

02:01:15.513 --> 02:01:18.098
Go on, Sergeant Hardy!

02:01:28.283 --> 02:01:30.026
Bring 'em home!

02:01:30.110 --> 02:01:32.519
Hardy! Hardy! Hardy!

02:01:37.856 --> 02:01:38.841
What was that?

02:01:45.546 --> 02:01:47.386
I'm never going to forgive myself.

02:01:47.511 --> 02:01:49.731
I'm never going to
bloody forgive myself.

02:01:53.345 --> 02:01:56.150
Sergeant Hardy, Sir.
It was booby-trapped.

02:01:56.822 --> 02:02:00.893
They was runnin' up the Union Jack,
Sir, up on that statue.

02:02:00.977 --> 02:02:02.532
It just went off, Sir.

02:02:03.926 --> 02:02:06.920
Sergeant Hardy climbed up,
Sir, just for a lark, Sir.

02:02:07.388 --> 02:02:09.126
It should've been me. It was my idea.

02:02:09.408 --> 02:02:11.568
-Sir, you don't wanna look.
-Ooh.

02:02:13.275 --> 02:02:14.164
Who's that girl?

02:02:14.830 --> 02:02:16.065
His fiancee, Sir.

02:02:17.796 --> 02:02:20.720
-Hardy's?
-He kept it a bit dark.

02:02:30.231 --> 02:02:30.780
Kip?

02:02:33.015 --> 02:02:34.406
Kip, it's me.

02:02:36.651 --> 02:02:38.776
I'm so sorry about what happened.

02:02:40.926 --> 02:02:43.161
Can I talk to you? Kip?

02:02:45.820 --> 02:02:48.396
Kip, why won't you talk to me?

02:02:51.765 --> 02:02:52.987
Oh, Kip.

02:02:58.262 --> 02:02:59.948
Oh, let me come in!

02:03:26.813 --> 02:03:30.067
Hana tells me you're leaving.

02:03:30.326 --> 02:03:32.026
There's going to be trials.

02:03:32.783 --> 02:03:34.205
They want me to interpret.

02:03:35.119 --> 02:03:37.519
Don't they know I'm
allergic to courtrooms?

02:03:42.459 --> 02:03:43.242
So...

02:03:46.735 --> 02:03:48.690
I come across the hospital convoy.

02:03:49.451 --> 02:03:50.804
They're looking for this stuff.

02:03:51.635 --> 02:03:53.550
This nurse, Mary,

02:03:54.054 --> 02:03:56.185
tells me about you and Hana...

02:03:56.557 --> 02:03:58.738
hiding in some monastery in...

02:03:58.885 --> 02:04:01.221
What do you call it? Retreat?

02:04:02.354 --> 02:04:04.690
How you came out of the desert...

02:04:04.815 --> 02:04:08.819
and you were burned and you
didn't remember your name,

02:04:09.215 --> 02:04:11.935
but you knew the words to
every song that ever was...

02:04:12.019 --> 02:04:15.725
and you had one possession:
a copy of Herodotus.

02:04:16.858 --> 02:04:18.287
And it was filled...

02:04:18.614 --> 02:04:20.782
with letters and cuttings.

02:04:21.915 --> 02:04:23.527
Then I knew it was you.

02:04:28.503 --> 02:04:29.143
Me?

02:04:41.239 --> 02:04:42.254
I saw you...

02:04:43.039 --> 02:04:46.982
writing in that book at
the embassy in Cairo...

02:04:48.692 --> 02:04:51.208
when I had thumbs and you had a face...

02:04:52.696 --> 02:04:53.674
and a name.

02:04:54.782 --> 02:04:55.830
I see.

02:04:58.212 --> 02:05:00.960
Before you went over to the Germans,
before you found

02:05:01.043 --> 02:05:03.117
a way to get Rommel's
spy across the desert

02:05:03.200 --> 02:05:05.057
and inside British headquarters.

02:05:05.930 --> 02:05:07.804
He took some pretty good photographs.

02:05:07.888 --> 02:05:10.465
I saw mine in that
torture room in Tobruk.

02:05:11.217 --> 02:05:14.456
So, it made an impression.

02:05:15.552 --> 02:05:18.689
I had to get back to the desert.
I'd made a promise.

02:05:20.140 --> 02:05:22.142
The rest meant nothing to me.

02:05:22.592 --> 02:05:23.525
What did you say?

02:05:24.690 --> 02:05:28.393
That the rest... meant nothing to me.

02:05:28.487 --> 02:05:30.641
There was a result to what you did.

02:05:31.167 --> 02:05:34.957
It wasn't just another expedition.
It did this.

02:05:35.464 --> 02:05:37.713
If the British hadn't
unearthed that photographer,

02:05:37.797 --> 02:05:39.660
thousands of people could have died.

02:05:39.785 --> 02:05:43.674
Thousands of people did die.
Just different people.

02:05:43.787 --> 02:05:47.056
-Yes, like Madox.
-What?

02:05:47.481 --> 02:05:50.462
You know he shot himself, your partner,

02:05:50.546 --> 02:05:52.299
-when he found out you were a spy.
-What?

02:05:56.713 --> 02:05:59.943
Madox thought I was a spy? No.

02:06:00.097 --> 02:06:02.421
No, I was never a spy.

02:06:03.616 --> 02:06:05.853
It's ghastly. It's like a witch hunt.

02:06:05.978 --> 02:06:08.355
Anybody remotely foreign
is suddenly a spy.

02:06:08.480 --> 02:06:10.645
-So watch out.
-Right.

02:06:11.538 --> 02:06:13.719
We didn't care about countries, did we?

02:06:14.445 --> 02:06:16.947
Brits, Arabs, Hungarians, Germans...

02:06:17.354 --> 02:06:20.136
None of that mattered, did it?
It was something finer than that.

02:06:21.310 --> 02:06:22.305
Yes, it was.

02:06:24.987 --> 02:06:27.041
I'll leave the plane in Kufra oasis.

02:06:27.578 --> 02:06:29.412
-So, if you need it...
-Right.

02:06:29.914 --> 02:06:31.967
Hard to know how long
one's talking about.

02:06:32.337 --> 02:06:34.159
We might all be back in a month or two.

02:06:39.553 --> 02:06:40.294
Hmm.

02:06:45.293 --> 02:06:48.376
I have to teach myself not to
read too much into everything.

02:06:50.129 --> 02:06:51.603
It comes of too long having to read

02:06:51.687 --> 02:06:53.377
so much into hardly anything at all.

02:06:59.336 --> 02:07:00.752
Goodbye, my friend.

02:07:07.911 --> 02:07:09.102
There is no God.

02:07:11.392 --> 02:07:13.045
But I hope someone looks after you.

02:07:14.963 --> 02:07:16.510
In case you're still wondering,

02:07:18.509 --> 02:07:20.442
this is called a supra-sternal notch.

02:07:25.518 --> 02:07:28.100
Come and visit us in Dorset
when all this nonsense is over.

02:07:34.958 --> 02:07:36.241
You'll never come to Dorset.

02:07:46.870 --> 02:07:49.403
So, you didn't know Madox shot himself.

02:07:54.447 --> 02:07:55.462
No.

02:07:56.362 --> 02:07:58.446
And you didn't kill the Cliftons?

02:08:07.643 --> 02:08:08.368
Sh...

02:08:14.868 --> 02:08:15.709
She...

02:08:19.710 --> 02:08:20.721
She die...

02:08:23.444 --> 02:08:25.029
She... I can't.

02:08:28.537 --> 02:08:29.409
Well,

02:08:31.665 --> 02:08:33.208
maybe I did.

02:08:38.580 --> 02:08:39.892
Maybe I did.

02:08:47.625 --> 02:08:50.378
I was packing up our base camp...

02:08:50.462 --> 02:08:52.392
at the Cave of Swimmers.

02:08:52.930 --> 02:08:57.518
Clifton had offered to fly
down from Cairo to collect me.

02:08:58.093 --> 02:09:00.944
He flew like a madman always,

02:09:01.028 --> 02:09:03.085
so I... I took no notice.

02:09:12.422 --> 02:09:13.958
Aaah!

02:09:39.378 --> 02:09:40.372
Katharine?

02:09:42.265 --> 02:09:45.206
Dear God,
Katharine, what are you doing here?

02:09:46.198 --> 02:09:48.798
I can't get out. I can't move.

02:09:53.163 --> 02:09:54.834
'Surprise, ' he said.

02:09:57.042 --> 02:09:58.325
Poor Geoffrey.

02:09:59.795 --> 02:10:02.666
He knew. He must've known all the time.

02:10:04.591 --> 02:10:07.208
He was shouting, 'I love you, Katharine.
I love you so much.'

02:10:10.514 --> 02:10:11.737
Is he badly hurt?

02:10:14.791 --> 02:10:15.878
I have to get you out.

02:10:16.770 --> 02:10:19.120
-Please don't move me.
-I have to get you out.

02:10:19.273 --> 02:10:22.783
-It hurts too much.
-I know, darling, I know. I'm sorry.

02:10:23.110 --> 02:10:23.848
Come on.

02:10:27.760 --> 02:10:28.574
Now!

02:10:46.800 --> 02:10:48.357
Why did you hate me?

02:10:49.219 --> 02:10:49.862
What?

02:10:53.925 --> 02:10:56.185
Don't you know you drove everybody mad?

02:10:56.269 --> 02:10:59.027
Shh. Don't talk.

02:11:00.123 --> 02:11:02.149
You speak so many bloody languages...

02:11:02.233 --> 02:11:03.806
and you never want to talk.

02:11:10.824 --> 02:11:14.036
-You're wearing the thimble.
-Of course.

02:11:14.804 --> 02:11:16.123
You idiot.

02:11:16.830 --> 02:11:19.222
I always wear it. I've always worn it.

02:11:20.831 --> 02:11:22.123
I've always loved you.

02:11:58.938 --> 02:12:00.272
It's so cold.

02:12:00.598 --> 02:12:02.757
I know. I'm sorry.

02:12:05.749 --> 02:12:06.720
I'll make a fire.

02:12:13.204 --> 02:12:15.055
Did you get Geoffrey out of the plane?

02:12:15.180 --> 02:12:18.333
-Yes, I did.
-Good. That's good. Thank you.

02:12:24.012 --> 02:12:25.107
Listen to me, Katharine.

02:12:26.478 --> 02:12:27.693
You've broken your ankle...

02:12:27.818 --> 02:12:29.634
and I'm going to have
to try and bind it.

02:12:30.446 --> 02:12:32.529
I think you've also
broken your wrist...

02:12:33.073 --> 02:12:35.859
and maybe some ribs, which is
why it's hurting you to breathe.

02:12:36.855 --> 02:12:39.246
I'm going to have to walk to El Taj.

02:12:40.094 --> 02:12:43.418
Although, given all the traffic
in the desert these days,

02:12:43.522 --> 02:12:46.732
I'm bound to bump into
one army or another.

02:12:47.482 --> 02:12:50.212
And then I'll come back
and you'll be fine.

02:12:51.602 --> 02:12:52.509
You promise?

02:12:54.138 --> 02:12:55.679
I wouldn't want to die here.

02:12:56.930 --> 02:12:58.356
I don't want to die in the desert.

02:13:03.658 --> 02:13:06.183
I've always had a rather
elaborate funeral in mind.

02:13:08.025 --> 02:13:09.382
Particular hymns.

02:13:10.139 --> 02:13:12.291
And I know exactly where
I want to be buried.

02:13:14.865 --> 02:13:16.557
In our garden, where I grew up...

02:13:18.727 --> 02:13:20.242
with a view of the sea.

02:13:22.088 --> 02:13:23.831
So promise me you'll come back for me.

02:13:25.462 --> 02:13:26.295
I promise...

02:13:27.524 --> 02:13:28.570
I'll come back for you.

02:13:31.128 --> 02:13:32.326
I promise...

02:13:33.967 --> 02:13:35.188
I'll never leave you.

02:13:41.120 --> 02:13:42.428
You have plenty of water...

02:13:43.394 --> 02:13:45.084
and, um, food.

02:13:47.352 --> 02:13:48.915
I'll open them for you.

02:13:54.311 --> 02:13:55.300
A good read.

02:13:59.917 --> 02:14:01.086
Don't waste this.

02:14:06.520 --> 02:14:07.793
Will you bury Geoffrey?

02:14:12.715 --> 02:14:14.033
I know he's dead.

02:14:18.322 --> 02:14:19.761
I'm sorry, Katharine.

02:14:21.682 --> 02:14:22.385
I know.

02:14:30.894 --> 02:14:31.954
Every night...

02:14:34.111 --> 02:14:35.560
I cut out my heart.

02:14:41.659 --> 02:14:43.732
But in the morning it was full again.

02:14:51.554 --> 02:14:52.476
Darling.

02:14:54.681 --> 02:14:55.698
My darling.

02:15:23.619 --> 02:15:26.315
# You'd better be ready
about half past 8:00 #

02:15:26.914 --> 02:15:28.992
# Now, honey
Don't you be late #

02:15:29.076 --> 02:15:31.913
# I'm going to be there when
the band starts playing #

02:15:32.211 --> 02:15:34.254
# Remember
When we get there, honey #

02:15:34.380 --> 02:15:36.924
# An invitation to
the strutter's ball #

02:15:37.091 --> 02:15:39.134
# A very swell affair #

02:15:39.495 --> 02:15:41.637
# All the highbrows will be there #

02:15:41.804 --> 02:15:45.432
# I'll be down to get you in a taxi,
honey #

02:15:45.557 --> 02:15:48.542
# I stopped at noon and at twilight #

02:15:49.770 --> 02:15:53.547
Three days there on foot, I told her,

02:15:54.229 --> 02:15:57.830
and three hours back by car.

02:16:00.322 --> 02:16:01.640
Don't go anywhere.

02:16:03.867 --> 02:16:04.786
I'll be back.

02:16:08.912 --> 02:16:09.849
I'll be back.

02:16:28.046 --> 02:16:29.749
Just walked in from the desert, Sir.

02:16:31.544 --> 02:16:32.306
Morning.

02:16:46.761 --> 02:16:49.620
Dear golly,
where have you come from then?

02:16:51.245 --> 02:16:53.041
There's been an accident.

02:16:53.862 --> 02:16:55.146
I need a doctor...

02:16:55.835 --> 02:16:58.818
to come with me,
and I need to borrow this car.

02:16:59.512 --> 02:17:00.462
I'll pay, of course.

02:17:00.546 --> 02:17:04.662
-And I need... I need morphine.
-May I see your papers, Sir?

02:17:06.537 --> 02:17:07.291
What?

02:17:07.505 --> 02:17:09.574
If I could just see some
form of identification.

02:17:10.893 --> 02:17:14.204
I'm sorry, I'm not making sense.
Forgive me, I... I'm not...

02:17:14.438 --> 02:17:16.680
I've been walking and...

02:17:17.023 --> 02:17:20.696
A woman is badly injured at the
Gilf Kabir,

02:17:21.102 --> 02:17:21.903
the Cave of Swimmers.

02:17:21.986 --> 02:17:24.573
I'm a member of the Royal
Geographical Society.

02:17:25.013 --> 02:17:25.796
Right.

02:17:27.450 --> 02:17:30.829
Now, if I could... just take your name.

02:17:33.915 --> 02:17:38.504
Count Laszlo de Almasy.

02:17:40.798 --> 02:17:44.884
'Almasy.'
Would you mind spelling that for me?

02:17:44.968 --> 02:17:48.168
-Look, listen to me, will you?
-What nationality would that be?

02:17:48.378 --> 02:17:52.187
A woman is dying. My wife is dying.

02:17:52.388 --> 02:17:55.306
I have been... walking...

02:17:58.145 --> 02:18:00.566
I have been walking for three days.

02:18:00.734 --> 02:18:03.111
I do not want to spell my name.

02:18:03.278 --> 02:18:06.477
-I want you to give me this car.
-I understand you're agitated.

02:18:06.603 --> 02:18:09.660
Perhaps if you'd like to sit down,
I can radio back to HQ.

02:18:10.055 --> 02:18:14.620
No. No, don't... Don't radio anybody!

02:18:14.959 --> 02:18:18.884
Just give me the fucking car!

02:19:18.603 --> 02:19:22.513
Stop the car, please. A woman is dying!

02:19:22.597 --> 02:19:24.824
Listen, Fritz, if I have to
listen to another word from you,

02:19:24.907 --> 02:19:26.596
I'm going to give you
a fucking good hiding!

02:19:26.680 --> 02:19:29.614
Fritz?
What are you talking about, Fritz?

02:19:29.698 --> 02:19:31.117
Well, that's your name, isn't it?

02:19:31.200 --> 02:19:33.415
Count Fuckin' Asshole Von Bismarck!

02:19:33.500 --> 02:19:35.816
-What's that supposed to be, Irish?
-Please!

02:19:35.925 --> 02:19:39.763
You have to listen! Katharine!

02:19:40.320 --> 02:19:42.557
Katharine!

02:19:56.262 --> 02:19:57.287
Excuse me.

02:19:57.915 --> 02:20:00.771
-I also need to use the lavatory.
-You'll have to wait.

02:20:00.938 --> 02:20:03.756
-It's urgent.
-Sarge!

02:20:05.337 --> 02:20:07.861
Sarge, Jerry wants to use the lav.

02:20:08.381 --> 02:20:09.657
Says it's urgent.

02:20:12.566 --> 02:20:16.141
-Where are we going, please?
-Oh, up north to the coast.

02:20:16.225 --> 02:20:18.644
Benghazi. Soon be there.

02:20:19.018 --> 02:20:20.577
You can get your boat back home then.

02:20:21.723 --> 02:20:25.091
All right, go on then.
Here, you take him.

02:20:25.175 --> 02:20:27.883
I've been up and down
this bloody train all day.

02:20:43.771 --> 02:20:44.916
It doesn't open.

02:21:00.860 --> 02:21:01.931
Aaah!

02:21:56.334 --> 02:21:57.414
So yes,

02:21:59.503 --> 02:22:02.280
she died because of me.

02:22:05.498 --> 02:22:06.746
Because I loved her.

02:22:11.453 --> 02:22:12.405
Because I...

02:22:16.833 --> 02:22:18.417
Because I had the wrong name.

02:22:28.581 --> 02:22:32.793
-And you never got back to the cave?
-I did get back.

02:22:33.686 --> 02:22:35.540
I kept my promise.

02:22:37.714 --> 02:22:39.982
I was assisted by the Germans.

02:22:40.931 --> 02:22:42.761
There was a... a trade.

02:22:43.392 --> 02:22:46.518
I had our expedition maps.

02:22:46.969 --> 02:22:49.857
And after the British
made me their enemy,

02:22:50.050 --> 02:22:53.734
I gave their enemy our maps.

02:23:06.571 --> 02:23:08.380
So I got back to the desert...

02:23:09.096 --> 02:23:10.243
and to Katharine...

02:23:11.587 --> 02:23:13.797
in Madox's English plane...

02:23:13.964 --> 02:23:15.363
with German gasoline.

02:23:20.932 --> 02:23:23.721
When I arrived in Italy,

02:23:23.805 --> 02:23:26.268
on my medical chart they wrote,

02:23:26.682 --> 02:23:27.882
'English Patient.'

02:23:29.489 --> 02:23:30.581
Isn't that funny?

02:23:32.195 --> 02:23:35.084
After all that, I became English.

02:23:38.997 --> 02:23:42.071
You get to the morning and the
poison leaks away, doesn't it?

02:23:46.723 --> 02:23:48.050
Black nights.

02:23:52.969 --> 02:23:55.700
-I thought I would kill you.
-You can't kill me.

02:23:57.586 --> 02:23:59.214
I died years ago.

02:24:03.681 --> 02:24:05.615
No, I can't kill you now.

02:24:25.536 --> 02:24:28.639
We've been posted. North of Florence.

02:24:35.323 --> 02:24:36.974
I was thinking yesterday...

02:24:38.632 --> 02:24:39.582
yesterday...

02:24:41.218 --> 02:24:42.521
The patient and Hardy.

02:24:43.762 --> 02:24:45.447
They're everything that's
good about England.

02:24:47.889 --> 02:24:49.643
I couldn't even say what that was.

02:24:52.312 --> 02:24:54.769
We didn't exchange two personal words,

02:24:55.816 --> 02:24:58.416
and we've been together
through some terrible things.

02:24:58.811 --> 02:25:00.240
Some terrible things.

02:25:02.059 --> 02:25:04.105
He was engaged to a
girl in the village.

02:25:05.355 --> 02:25:06.138
I mean...

02:25:07.870 --> 02:25:11.419
And us, he never once...

02:25:12.153 --> 02:25:14.096
He didn't ask me if
I could spin the ball

02:25:14.209 --> 02:25:16.408
at cricket or kama sutra or...

02:25:30.851 --> 02:25:32.947
I don't even know what
I'm talking about.

02:25:34.509 --> 02:25:35.779
You loved him.

02:27:00.065 --> 02:27:01.105
Katharine.

02:27:15.706 --> 02:27:17.188
I'm still here.

02:27:19.793 --> 02:27:21.128
You'd better be.

02:27:22.504 --> 02:27:24.148
Don't depend on it, will you?

02:27:26.592 --> 02:27:29.430
That little bit of air in my lungs,

02:27:30.054 --> 02:27:33.170
each day it gets less and less.

02:27:35.225 --> 02:27:36.426
Which is all right.

02:27:37.603 --> 02:27:38.817
It's quite all right.

02:27:42.149 --> 02:27:44.590
I've been speaking to Caravaggio,

02:27:45.682 --> 02:27:47.165
my research assistant.

02:27:48.685 --> 02:27:51.913
He tells me there's a
ghost in the cloisters.

02:27:53.494 --> 02:27:54.528
I can join him.

02:27:58.085 --> 02:28:00.098
-Hana!
-It's the boy.

02:28:25.584 --> 02:28:27.573
I'll always go back to that church.

02:28:28.570 --> 02:28:30.108
Look at my paintings.

02:28:35.244 --> 02:28:37.362
I'll always go back to that church.

02:28:39.692 --> 02:28:40.971
So one day we'll meet.

02:30:33.827 --> 02:30:34.473
Thank you.

02:30:46.500 --> 02:30:48.564
Read to me, will you?

02:30:54.633 --> 02:30:55.857
Read me to sleep.

02:31:20.117 --> 02:31:21.462
'My darling,

02:31:22.828 --> 02:31:24.431
'I'm waiting for you.'

02:31:25.664 --> 02:31:27.933
'How long is a day in the dark?'

02:31:29.463 --> 02:31:30.477
'Or a week?'

02:31:40.036 --> 02:31:41.653
'The fire is gone now...

02:31:42.222 --> 02:31:45.142
and I'm horr... horribly cold.'

02:31:47.102 --> 02:31:49.004
I really ought to drag myself outside,

02:31:49.088 --> 02:31:50.267
but then there'd be the sun.

02:31:53.117 --> 02:31:54.860
I'm afraid I waste the light...

02:31:54.985 --> 02:31:57.310
on the paintings and
on writing these words.

02:32:01.613 --> 02:32:02.582
We die.

02:32:04.074 --> 02:32:05.357
'We die.

02:32:05.746 --> 02:32:08.916
'We die rich with lovers and tribes,

02:32:09.724 --> 02:32:11.746
'tastes we have swallowed,

02:32:12.961 --> 02:32:15.756
'bodies we have entered...

02:32:16.193 --> 02:32:18.092
and swum up like rivers.'

02:32:19.229 --> 02:32:20.763
Fears we've hidden in,

02:32:21.863 --> 02:32:23.418
like this wretched cave.

02:32:29.853 --> 02:32:31.883
I want all this marked on my body.

02:32:34.817 --> 02:32:36.424
We're the real countries.

02:32:37.547 --> 02:32:39.966
Not the boundaries drawn on maps,

02:32:40.807 --> 02:32:42.499
the names of powerful men.

02:32:53.877 --> 02:32:57.233
I know you'll come and carry me
out into the palace of winds.

02:33:05.723 --> 02:33:07.243
That's all I've wanted,

02:33:08.767 --> 02:33:10.839
to walk in such a place with you,

02:33:12.771 --> 02:33:14.037
with friends.

02:33:15.733 --> 02:33:17.274
An Earth without maps.

02:33:23.574 --> 02:33:25.184
'The lamp's gone out,

02:33:26.410 --> 02:33:27.478
'and I'm writing...

02:33:29.913 --> 02:33:31.253
in the darkness.'

02:34:35.121 --> 02:34:36.248
Hana?

02:34:37.648 --> 02:34:39.317
Hana, come on!

02:34:42.453 --> 02:34:43.216
Hana,

02:34:46.247 --> 02:34:47.616
this is Gioia.

02:34:47.700 --> 02:34:49.011
-Buon giorno.
-Buon giorno.

02:34:50.828 --> 02:34:52.246
She'll take you as far as Florence.

02:34:52.571 --> 02:34:53.725
I can get in back.
